1
00:01:36,610 --> 00:01:39,910
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:40,060 --> 00:01:42,000
[Episode 14]

3
00:01:42,229 --> 00:01:44,030
Don't watch so many soap operas.

4
00:01:44,430 --> 00:01:45,990
You're already not smart.

5
00:01:46,009 --> 00:01:47,590
The more you watch, the dumber you get.

6
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:49,850
What are you thinking about? Go to sleep!

7
00:01:50,539 --> 00:01:51,550
Who are you talking about?

8
00:01:51,550 --> 00:01:52,350
Say that again!

9
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:53,640
Who are you calling dumb?

10
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:55,450
-Apologize!
-Sorry. Sorry.

11
00:02:07,590 --> 00:02:08,460
Fenghua.

12
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:09,910
I thought of

13
00:02:09,910 --> 00:02:11,100
a position in my future company

14
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:12,190
that's perfect for you.

15
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:12,870
What is it?

16
00:02:12,870 --> 00:02:13,800
Security guard.

17
00:02:13,830 --> 00:02:14,550
It's the perfect job

18
00:02:14,550 --> 00:02:15,430
for you.

19
00:02:15,460 --> 00:02:17,290
Sure, I'll keep you safe!

20
00:02:18,390 --> 00:02:19,230
Go get some rest.

21
00:02:19,230 --> 00:02:19,829
Good night.

22
00:02:19,829 --> 00:02:20,670
Good night.

23
00:02:44,390 --> 00:02:45,270
Grandma.

24
00:02:45,670 --> 00:02:46,430
You're back?

25
00:02:49,430 --> 00:02:50,950
Have you had dinner?

26
00:02:51,190 --> 00:02:52,310
Yes.

27
00:03:15,990 --> 00:03:17,120
Siyi.

28
00:03:17,670 --> 00:03:18,770
You must be tired.

29
00:03:19,630 --> 00:03:21,360
I saved some dinner for you.

30
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:24,630
When will Chen Rui be discharged

31
00:03:24,630 --> 00:03:26,310
from the hospital?

32
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:27,540
Soon.

33
00:03:29,470 --> 00:03:30,270
Once he's discharged,

34
00:03:30,270 --> 00:03:32,630
you won't have to work so hard, right?

35
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:36,710
Alright.

36
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:39,810
If you're tired, go to bed.

37
00:03:40,070 --> 00:03:41,690
I'll go put away the food.

38
00:03:43,270 --> 00:03:43,900
Grandma.

39
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:47,630
Come here.

40
00:03:53,990 --> 00:03:54,870
What's wrong?

41
00:04:00,070 --> 00:04:01,600
I want to ask you something.

42
00:04:02,190 --> 00:04:04,140
How can you tell

43
00:04:04,140 --> 00:04:05,550
if someone likes you?

44
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:08,670
I'm not asking for myself.

45
00:04:08,670 --> 00:04:10,000
It's for a classmate.

46
00:04:15,340 --> 00:04:16,560
Well, about that,

47
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:19,240
you don't need to think too hard about it.

48
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:20,589
If he likes you,

49
00:04:20,589 --> 00:04:22,890
you'll naturally know.

50
00:04:23,590 --> 00:04:24,630
It's like

51
00:04:24,790 --> 00:04:26,240
cooking rice.

52
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:30,470
When the rice is ready, you can smell its aroma.

53
00:04:33,710 --> 00:04:35,010
What if

54
00:04:35,590 --> 00:04:37,720
he likes someone else at the same time?

55
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:40,930
That won't happen.

56
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:43,640
If he likes you,

57
00:04:44,020 --> 00:04:45,700
he'll only have eyes for you.

58
00:04:49,110 --> 00:04:50,780
Your grandpa and I

59
00:04:50,870 --> 00:04:52,770
fell in love at first sight.

60
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:53,950
At that time,

61
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:56,430
he only had eyes for me.

62
00:04:57,180 --> 00:04:59,510
He followed me everywhere I went.

63
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:01,200
He was so clingy.

64
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,290
In the future,

65
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:08,110
you should find someone like that,

66
00:05:08,990 --> 00:05:10,850
someone who only has eyes for you.

67
00:05:17,510 --> 00:05:18,990
My little darling,

68
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:20,790
you have something on your mind.

69
00:05:21,990 --> 00:05:23,030
I told you

70
00:05:23,070 --> 00:05:24,300
it's not about me.

71
00:05:24,980 --> 00:05:27,290
Okay. Whatever you say.

72
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:31,210
I'll go put away the food.

73
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:51,730
[Joint Exam]

74
00:05:51,950 --> 00:05:54,110
Class, I hope

75
00:05:54,110 --> 00:05:56,590
everyone can take today's joint exam seriously.

76
00:05:56,590 --> 00:05:58,330
Let's take this opportunity

77
00:05:58,550 --> 00:06:00,050
to find out

78
00:06:00,230 --> 00:06:02,790
how wide the gap between No. 1 High School and us is.

79
00:06:02,790 --> 00:06:04,790
Show the excellence of No. 1 High School.

80
00:06:04,790 --> 00:06:06,710
Let everyone know that our school

81
00:06:06,710 --> 00:06:08,540
can never be surpassed.

82
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:11,970
You should have some pride.

83
00:06:12,350 --> 00:06:14,270
You can't lose too badly.

84
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,420
Francis Bacon once said,

85
00:06:17,470 --> 00:06:19,580
"Histories make men wise;

86
00:06:19,610 --> 00:06:21,620
the mathematics, subtle."

87
00:06:22,940 --> 00:06:25,510
There's an old Chinese saying

88
00:06:26,330 --> 00:06:30,160
that goes, "Victory and defeat are both common in war."

89
00:06:30,340 --> 00:06:31,940
Don't be too nervous.

90
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:33,450
Relax.

91
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,040
Just do it as usual.

92
00:06:35,070 --> 00:06:36,820
If you ace this exam,

93
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:39,159
I'll ask the principal to treat you to a meal!

94
00:06:39,159 --> 00:06:42,180
[Joint Exam]

95
00:06:42,260 --> 00:06:43,070
Xie.

96
00:06:43,110 --> 00:06:44,480
We usually only do retail,

97
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,440
not wholesale.

98
00:06:45,590 --> 00:06:47,909
If we hadn't been friends for so many years,

99
00:06:47,909 --> 00:06:48,830
-I wouldn't…
-That's why I keep saying

100
00:06:48,830 --> 00:06:50,350
we're good buddies.

101
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:51,470
Right? Good buddies.

102
00:06:51,470 --> 00:06:52,270
Yeah.

103
00:06:52,270 --> 00:06:53,030
The water…

104
00:06:53,030 --> 00:06:53,790
I think…

105
00:06:53,790 --> 00:06:55,190
Get a few more cases of it.

106
00:06:55,230 --> 00:06:56,040
A few more.

107
00:06:56,060 --> 00:06:56,590
How many cases of water?

108
00:06:56,590 --> 00:06:57,710
Seven or eight.

109
00:06:57,830 --> 00:06:58,240
Okay.

110
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,030
Eight cases, right?

111
00:06:59,030 --> 00:06:59,830
Eight cases of water.

112
00:06:59,830 --> 00:07:00,670
The bread…

113
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:01,800
Which brand is good?

114
00:07:02,030 --> 00:07:02,590
This one.

115
00:07:03,030 --> 00:07:03,670
It's new.

116
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:04,430
Trust me.

117
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:05,210
Really?

118
00:07:05,460 --> 00:07:06,750
Yes. It sells very well.

119
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:08,150
Lao'er, take six boxes of them.

120
00:07:08,150 --> 00:07:09,030
Six boxes.

121
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:09,960
Okay. Six boxes.

122
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:10,560
Six boxes of bread.

123
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,030
Yeah.

124
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:11,790
Okay.

125
00:07:13,030 --> 00:07:14,340
This kind of thing doesn't sell well.

126
00:07:14,340 --> 00:07:15,530
Don't buy so many.

127
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:17,500
Back when we were seafaring,

128
00:07:17,940 --> 00:07:20,050
bottled water and bread

129
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:21,420
were necessities.

130
00:07:21,910 --> 00:07:22,710
Do as I say.

131
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:24,150
Supermarkets on land

132
00:07:24,150 --> 00:07:26,260
are pretty much the same as those on water.

133
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:27,020
Understand?

134
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:28,440
My judgment should be pretty accurate.

135
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:29,570
Xie.

136
00:07:29,790 --> 00:07:31,470
I just got this vinegar

137
00:07:31,470 --> 00:07:32,240
and soy sauce.

138
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,030
They're new products.

139
00:07:33,030 --> 00:07:33,790
New products?

140
00:07:33,790 --> 00:07:34,740
Take a look.

141
00:07:34,909 --> 00:07:36,070
Seafarers often cook

142
00:07:36,070 --> 00:07:36,640
on ships.

143
00:07:36,670 --> 00:07:37,909
Yeah. Look.

144
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:38,820
Soy sauce.

145
00:07:38,990 --> 00:07:40,030
How many boxes now?

146
00:07:40,030 --> 00:07:40,790
Five.

147
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:41,670
Is it expensive?

148
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:42,310
Hold it.

149
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,540
No. It sells well.

150
00:07:43,790 --> 00:07:44,810
It sells well?

151
00:07:45,110 --> 00:07:45,909
Six boxes.

152
00:07:45,909 --> 00:07:46,590
Alright.

153
00:07:49,110 --> 00:07:50,570
Sir, we'll take the check.

154
00:07:51,020 --> 00:07:52,220
Boss Xie, there's no more room.

155
00:07:52,220 --> 00:07:53,150
The cart is full.

156
00:08:01,980 --> 00:08:03,700
Here! Here!

157
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,480
Come here!

158
00:08:06,860 --> 00:08:07,990
What would you like?

159
00:08:08,020 --> 00:08:08,830
Instant noodles.

160
00:08:08,710 --> 00:08:15,780
[Floating Supermarket]

161
00:08:10,230 --> 00:08:10,710
Well,

162
00:08:10,710 --> 00:08:11,670
they're right here.

163
00:08:11,670 --> 00:08:12,710
Instant noodles.

164
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:13,830
Here.

165
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:14,470
Catch.

166
00:08:14,470 --> 00:08:15,350
One, two.

167
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:18,150
Anything else?

168
00:08:18,150 --> 00:08:18,790
Boss Xie?

169
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:20,430
Xie Tiancheng?

170
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:25,070
[Floating Supermarket]

171
00:08:22,690 --> 00:08:23,420
Yes, it's me.

172
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:25,230
You're still in the shipping business?

173
00:08:25,230 --> 00:08:26,110
What else can I do?

174
00:08:26,110 --> 00:08:28,110
It's the only thing I know in my life.

175
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:29,960
Why are you selling things?

176
00:08:30,130 --> 00:08:31,660
It was Xia Lao'er's idea.

177
00:08:32,380 --> 00:08:33,159
Just for fun.

178
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:36,049
Is this supermarket profitable?

179
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:38,020
This ship isn't big anyway.

180
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:39,799
So even if we lose money, it won't be much.

181
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:40,659
Do you want anything else?

182
00:08:40,659 --> 00:08:42,400
Alright, give me a case of milk.

183
00:08:42,909 --> 00:08:43,909
Sure. Here you go.

184
00:08:45,350 --> 00:08:47,140
And some greens and eggplants.

185
00:08:47,310 --> 00:08:48,170
Here they are.

186
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:49,460
Two bags.

187
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:50,270
They're fresh.

188
00:08:50,270 --> 00:08:51,070
Fresh, right?

189
00:08:52,370 --> 00:08:53,220
Catch.

190
00:08:53,590 --> 00:08:54,710
Boss Xie?

191
00:08:54,710 --> 00:08:55,670
Hey.

192
00:08:55,670 --> 00:08:57,310
Hello, Boss Xie.

193
00:08:57,810 --> 00:09:00,340
How come you're selling goods now?

194
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:02,990
In the old days,

195
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:05,080
you'd have to shake a rattle drum.

196
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:06,030
While selling,

197
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:07,230
you should shout…

198
00:09:07,230 --> 00:09:08,670
Shut up if you're gonna be rude!

199
00:09:08,670 --> 00:09:11,040
It's alright. Take this laundry detergent.

200
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:11,870
No, no, no.

201
00:09:11,870 --> 00:09:13,310
Thank you, Boss Xie.

202
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:14,640
Look at you.

203
00:09:14,650 --> 00:09:15,590
How much is it?

204
00:09:15,590 --> 00:09:16,670
60 will do.

205
00:09:16,910 --> 00:09:17,830
Alright.

206
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:18,800
60.

207
00:09:19,590 --> 00:09:20,380
Here.

208
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:21,470
Got it.

209
00:09:21,510 --> 00:09:22,690
We're leaving, Boss Xie.

210
00:09:22,690 --> 00:09:23,790
Take care.

211
00:09:27,230 --> 00:09:28,010
Boss Xie.

212
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:31,240
They got those things at wholesale prices?

213
00:09:31,260 --> 00:09:33,390
We can't make much money this way.

214
00:09:34,650 --> 00:09:37,090
This is customer cultivation, you know?

215
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:39,770
It's not like they won't buy from us again.

216
00:09:40,620 --> 00:09:41,670
But…

217
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:44,860
Say what you want to say.

218
00:09:43,990 --> 00:09:47,490
[Floating Supermarket]

219
00:09:46,790 --> 00:09:48,100
I don't mean to judge.

220
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:49,060
I'm just saying that

221
00:09:49,060 --> 00:09:50,850
if you keep selling things like this,

222
00:09:50,850 --> 00:09:52,820
when you charge them the original price in the future,

223
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:54,530
they'll all complain it's too expensive.

224
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:55,640
Impossible.

225
00:09:55,660 --> 00:09:57,300
Lao'er, listen to me.

226
00:09:57,330 --> 00:09:58,270
Don't just

227
00:09:58,270 --> 00:10:00,020
focus on loose change.

228
00:10:00,050 --> 00:10:01,230
Think big, okay?

229
00:10:01,230 --> 00:10:02,610
Look at the bigger picture.

230
00:10:02,610 --> 00:10:03,710
The bigger picture.

231
00:10:03,710 --> 00:10:04,660
Come on, pack up.

232
00:10:04,660 --> 00:10:05,670
We're leaving.

233
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:06,410
Come on.

234
00:10:12,270 --> 00:10:14,320
You're back. Come and eat.

235
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:15,660
I'm not hungry.

236
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:18,030
It's so late. How can you not be hungry?

237
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:19,160
You go ahead and eat.

238
00:10:28,310 --> 00:10:29,280
What's wrong?

239
00:10:31,190 --> 00:10:32,790
Did you have a fight with Xie?

240
00:10:33,070 --> 00:10:33,710
No.

241
00:10:34,420 --> 00:10:36,450
If you don't tell me, I'll ask Haihong.

242
00:10:36,450 --> 00:10:37,050
Come back!

243
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:42,280
I really don't understand.

244
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,720
He's an expert at seafaring,

245
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:47,240
but he's never run a supermarket before.

246
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:49,080
He has no experience at all.

247
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,940
Can't he think carefully before making decisions?

248
00:10:52,330 --> 00:10:53,290
What did he do?

249
00:10:54,310 --> 00:10:55,240
You have no idea.

250
00:10:55,580 --> 00:10:57,600
When buying goods, he didn't care if they would sell or not.

251
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,970
He just grabbed whatever he wanted.

252
00:10:58,970 --> 00:11:00,200
I said they wouldn't sell,

253
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,730
but he insisted they would.

254
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:03,520
When it comes to selling,

255
00:11:03,550 --> 00:11:04,760
to make himself look good,

256
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,360
he sold at wholesale prices.

257
00:11:06,890 --> 00:11:08,150
After toiling the whole day,

258
00:11:08,150 --> 00:11:09,440
we didn't make a penny

259
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:10,720
and even lost 50 yuan.

260
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:12,470
That won't do.

261
00:11:12,650 --> 00:11:14,030
You need to talk to him about it.

262
00:11:14,030 --> 00:11:15,510
If you don't tell him, how will he know?

263
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:16,890
It's useless to talk to him.

264
00:11:16,890 --> 00:11:18,090
Would he listen to me?

265
00:11:19,050 --> 00:11:20,670
I told him those things wouldn't sell,

266
00:11:20,670 --> 00:11:21,890
but he insisted they would.

267
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:23,920
You know what he's like.

268
00:11:32,990 --> 00:11:34,320
Wait for a few more days.

269
00:11:35,430 --> 00:11:36,920
Give him a few days to adjust.

270
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:38,250
Maybe it'll get better.

271
00:11:41,070 --> 00:11:41,790
It's okay.

272
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:43,670
Don't worry.

273
00:11:46,130 --> 00:11:48,670
Mom, didn't you say we'd have mandarin fish for dinner?

274
00:11:48,670 --> 00:11:49,670
Where's the fish?

275
00:11:52,470 --> 00:11:53,350
No fish.

276
00:11:53,590 --> 00:11:54,620
Starting today,

277
00:11:54,670 --> 00:11:55,980
no meat for a month.

278
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:58,190
And you won't get any allowance this month.

279
00:11:58,190 --> 00:11:59,460
Why not?

280
00:11:59,630 --> 00:12:00,940
Because you're not studying hard enough.

281
00:12:00,940 --> 00:12:03,540
Keep arguing, and you won't get dinner either.

282
00:12:06,070 --> 00:12:06,790
Mom!

283
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:27,360
[Honghuai Bus Station]

284
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:36,980
[Honghuai Bus Station]

285
00:12:32,930 --> 00:12:33,960
Ge Siwei.

286
00:12:34,070 --> 00:12:35,130
Is Ge Siwei's family here?

287
00:12:35,130 --> 00:12:36,230
Here.

288
00:12:36,260 --> 00:12:37,400
Nice to meet you.

289
00:12:37,550 --> 00:12:38,390
You're Ge Siwei's family, right?

290
00:12:38,390 --> 00:12:39,120
Yes.

291
00:12:40,780 --> 00:12:41,430
That's me, right?

292
00:12:41,430 --> 00:12:42,260
You're in the photo.

293
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:43,140
Yes.

294
