00:24:12,410 --> 00:24:13,990
♫Time quietly flies by♫

584
00:24:14,810 --> 00:24:16,760
♫I'll never regret♫

585
00:24:15,710 --> 00:24:16,630
Come on.

586
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,920
♫The pride among the stars♫

587
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:24,040
♫Keep running♫

588
00:24:21,540 --> 00:24:21,990
Alright.

589
00:24:21,990 --> 00:24:23,120
Uncle Zhou,

590
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:25,010
your cooking is different today.

591
00:24:25,010 --> 00:24:25,990
How so?

592
00:24:25,210 --> 00:24:27,750
♫Blood burning hot♫

593
00:24:26,030 --> 00:24:27,550
It's completely different, not the usual taste.

594
00:24:27,550 --> 00:24:28,310
How does it taste today?

595
00:24:28,310 --> 00:24:29,240
It tastes happy.

596
00:24:29,510 --> 00:24:31,890
♫Blood burning hot♫

597
00:24:29,910 --> 00:24:31,120
You brat!

598
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:33,220
You know what happiness tastes like?

599
00:24:33,620 --> 00:24:34,420
Xie Wanghe.

600
00:24:34,550 --> 00:24:35,460
Sir.

601
00:24:37,190 --> 00:24:40,030
The idea of the test prep center was yours, wasn't it?

602
00:24:40,030 --> 00:24:40,770
Yes.

603
00:24:41,310 --> 00:24:42,950
I know when the school

604
00:24:42,950 --> 00:24:44,540
used your idea,

605
00:24:44,540 --> 00:24:45,550
you were a bit upset.

606
00:24:45,550 --> 00:24:46,510
No, no, no.

607
00:24:46,510 --> 00:24:47,590
Not at all.

608
00:24:47,590 --> 00:24:49,110
I know you did it for our good.

609
00:24:49,110 --> 00:24:50,230
Let me finish.

610
00:24:51,550 --> 00:24:53,210
At that time, No. 7 High School

611
00:24:53,430 --> 00:24:56,310
had been under pressure from other schools for many years.

612
00:24:56,310 --> 00:24:57,590
We felt ashamed.

613
00:24:58,510 --> 00:25:00,390
As teachers of the school,

614
00:25:00,390 --> 00:25:01,650
we were bitter inside.

615
00:25:01,710 --> 00:25:03,270
So I sincerely hope

616
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:05,540
you can understand our feelings.

617
00:25:05,630 --> 00:25:06,270
Of course.

618
00:25:06,270 --> 00:25:07,700
We totally understand.

619
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:07,950
Yes.

620
00:25:07,950 --> 00:25:08,390
Right?

621
00:25:08,390 --> 00:25:09,550
Yes.

622
00:25:09,550 --> 00:25:10,430
Thank you.

623
00:25:10,870 --> 00:25:13,670
Thank you for your hard work, teachers.

624
00:25:14,110 --> 00:25:17,730
[Security Post]

625
00:25:20,070 --> 00:25:22,110
Goodbye.

626
00:25:22,130 --> 00:25:23,790
Goodbye.

627
00:25:23,790 --> 00:25:24,670
Wait a moment.

628
00:25:24,670 --> 00:25:25,470
Okay.

629
00:25:25,470 --> 00:25:25,990
Say goodbye to your teacher.

630
00:25:25,990 --> 00:25:26,830
Goodbye.

631
00:25:26,830 --> 00:25:27,430
Goodbye.

632
00:25:30,950 --> 00:25:31,950
Have all the students left?

633
00:25:31,950 --> 00:25:33,750
Yes, all the students have left.

634
00:25:38,510 --> 00:25:39,430
Ge Siwei.

635
00:25:41,120 --> 00:25:42,590
Ge Siwei, come out!

636
00:25:42,590 --> 00:25:43,990
How dare you skip school?

637
00:25:46,550 --> 00:25:47,470
Ge Siwei.

638
00:25:48,430 --> 00:25:50,510
Come out. Where are you hiding?

639
00:25:56,350 --> 00:25:57,930
Siyi, what's wrong?

640
00:25:57,970 --> 00:25:59,010
Where's Siwei?

641
00:25:59,110 --> 00:26:00,210
He hasn't come back.

642
00:26:00,210 --> 00:26:01,270
I bought some meat

643
00:26:01,270 --> 00:26:02,710
to make shredded pork with green peppers for you two.

644
00:26:02,710 --> 00:26:04,830
He didn't go to school at all today.

645
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,350
Go look for him.

646
00:26:06,370 --> 00:26:07,130
Okay.

647
00:26:09,470 --> 00:26:10,070
That boy…

648
00:26:10,070 --> 00:26:10,750
Siwei.

649
00:26:12,790 --> 00:26:14,150
Slow down!

650
00:26:15,420 --> 00:26:16,470
Siyi, perfect timing.

651
00:26:16,470 --> 00:26:17,470
Let's go eat.

652
00:26:17,470 --> 00:26:19,000
I can't. I need to look for my brother.

653
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:19,910
What happened?

654
00:26:19,990 --> 00:26:21,230
When I went to pick him up today,

655
00:26:21,230 --> 00:26:22,990
his teacher told me he didn't even show up at school.

656
00:26:22,990 --> 00:26:24,030
He's not at home either.

657
00:26:24,030 --> 00:26:25,470
Skipping school on the first day?

658
00:26:25,470 --> 00:26:26,450
Impressive.

659
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:28,130
Where could he be if he's not at home?

660
00:26:28,130 --> 00:26:28,920
Wherever he wants.

661
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:31,380
It'd be better if he died and never came back.

662
00:26:31,430 --> 00:26:34,010
At his age, if he ran into child traffickers…

663
00:26:35,940 --> 00:26:37,040
That can't be.

664
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:38,150
Don't you remember?

665
00:26:38,150 --> 00:26:40,100
My grandma spent a lot of money to get that kid.

666
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:41,840
Your brother could be sold for even more.

667
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:42,480
Don't…

668
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:43,460
Don't scare her.

669
00:26:43,710 --> 00:26:44,650
It's okay.

670
00:26:44,670 --> 00:26:46,340
He's been missing for less than 72 hours.

671
00:26:46,340 --> 00:26:47,200
We can find him.

672
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:48,240
Report to the police first. Let's go.

673
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:48,830
Let's go.

674
00:26:57,300 --> 00:26:59,130
Don't worry too much. We'll find him.

675
00:26:59,130 --> 00:27:01,060
There are cameras everywhere now.

676
00:27:02,810 --> 00:27:04,000
It's okay, Siyi.

677
00:27:04,270 --> 00:27:05,630
Even if he was kidnapped by human traffickers,

678
00:27:05,630 --> 00:27:06,960
we could still find him.

679
00:27:08,330 --> 00:27:10,060
What if he was in a car accident?

680
00:27:11,180 --> 00:27:13,780
You might as well say he was attacked by wolves.

681
00:27:15,330 --> 00:27:17,590
I'll sew your mouth shut sooner or later.

682
00:27:18,980 --> 00:27:19,710
Siyi,

683
00:27:20,490 --> 00:27:21,150
are you hungry?

684
00:27:21,150 --> 00:27:22,750
Do you want something to eat?

685
00:27:30,490 --> 00:27:31,290
Here he comes.

686
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:36,980
Here. Take a look at the photo.

687
00:27:38,230 --> 00:27:39,600
Is this your brother?

688
00:27:42,950 --> 00:27:44,550
Yes, that's him.

689
00:27:44,830 --> 00:27:46,090
According to the surveillance footage,

690
00:27:46,090 --> 00:27:48,040
he left school early in the morning.

691
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:49,430
He went to the long-distance bus station

692
00:27:49,430 --> 00:27:52,030
and got on a bus with the license plate ending in 8732.

693
00:27:52,030 --> 00:27:53,720
The destination is Suqian.

694
00:27:54,380 --> 00:27:55,370
Suqian?

695
00:27:57,580 --> 00:27:58,700
He went home.

696
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:00,700
It's my mother's home.

697
00:28:27,230 --> 00:28:28,070
Officer,

698
00:28:28,110 --> 00:28:30,030
how long until we reach Suqian?

699
00:28:30,630 --> 00:28:33,160
It'll probably take about another half hour.

700
00:28:33,300 --> 00:28:34,750
Can we go faster?

701
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:37,000
There's a speed limit on the national highway.

702
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:38,350
Even a police car can't exceed the speed limit?

703
00:28:38,350 --> 00:28:39,870
Can't you shut up?

704
00:28:46,060 --> 00:28:48,080
[Police]

705
00:29:04,100 --> 00:29:05,100
Ge Siwei!

706
00:29:05,750 --> 00:29:06,550
Siyi.

707
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:12,390
Why did you hit me?

708
00:29:12,390 --> 00:29:13,870
I'll fight you to the end!

709
00:29:15,030 --> 00:29:15,990
This is her family business.

710
00:29:15,990 --> 00:29:17,310
Let her handle it herself.

711
00:29:17,310 --> 00:29:19,290
Why are you hitting me?

712
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:21,810
What were you thinking?

713
00:29:21,850 --> 00:29:23,420
What if you got lost?

714
00:29:29,030 --> 00:29:30,080
It hurts!

715
00:29:35,210 --> 00:29:38,260
I want Mom!

716
00:29:42,750 --> 00:29:44,660
Mom!

717
00:29:44,680 --> 00:29:46,280
You don't even have the keys?

718
00:29:46,770 --> 00:29:48,550
The lock has been changed.

719
00:29:49,650 --> 00:29:52,010
This house has probably been sold already.

720
00:29:52,010 --> 00:29:53,930
This isn't your home anymore!

721
00:29:56,110 --> 00:29:58,780
I want Mom!

722
00:29:59,710 --> 00:30:01,330
Mom!

723
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:05,500
I don't have a home.

724
00:30:09,230 --> 00:30:11,010
I don't have a home.

725
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:13,290
Mom.

726
00:30:14,950 --> 00:30:17,780
I want Mom.

727
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:21,410
I want Mom.

728
00:30:23,840 --> 00:30:25,600
Mom.

729
00:31:00,530 --> 00:31:01,560
Are you full?

730
00:31:03,110 --> 00:31:04,650
Let's go home.

731
00:31:05,010 --> 00:31:06,120
No.

732
00:31:06,230 --> 00:31:07,820
I want to find my mom.

733
00:31:28,670 --> 00:31:30,470
Actually, you've impressed me.

734
00:31:31,150 --> 00:31:33,020
I was just like you back then,

735
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,570
dumped at Grandma's house.

736
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:37,030
I thought about running away

737
00:31:37,030 --> 00:31:38,430
and going back to Mom too,

738
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:41,370
but I only dared to think about it.

739
00:31:41,370 --> 00:31:42,800
I never took action.

740
00:31:42,830 --> 00:31:44,270
You're braver than me.

741
00:31:45,740 --> 00:31:46,880
I take after my dad.

742
00:31:47,270 --> 00:31:48,580
My dad dares to do anything.

743
00:31:48,580 --> 00:31:50,240
Is that why he ended up in jail?

744
00:31:56,890 --> 00:31:57,940
Back then,

745
00:31:58,370 --> 00:31:59,850
I hated my mom very much.

746
00:32:01,030 --> 00:32:02,300
I always wondered

747
00:32:02,430 --> 00:32:03,670
why she abandoned her daughter

748
00:32:03,670 --> 00:32:04,730
after having a son.

749
00:32:06,590 --> 00:32:07,620
But then

750
00:32:07,630 --> 00:32:08,890
she abandoned you too.

751
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,510
I felt instantly better.

752
00:32:10,510 --> 00:32:11,990
My mom didn't abandon me!

753
00:32:11,990 --> 00:32:13,110
Why are you yelling?

754
00:32:13,110 --> 00:32:15,370
Do you think yelling can make her show up?

755
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:19,660
[Perfect Taste]

756
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,830
When you're a bit older,

757
00:32:24,830 --> 00:32:25,960
you'll understand.

758
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:27,480
Mom

759
00:32:27,510 --> 00:32:28,790
only loves herself.

760
00:32:31,020 --> 00:32:32,990
But the best thing she ever did

761
00:32:33,760 --> 00:32:35,750
was send me to live with Grandma.

762
00:32:36,260 --> 00:32:37,460
What do you mean?

763
00:32:41,300 --> 00:32:42,470
That yard

764
00:32:43,950 --> 00:32:45,030
is warm.

765
00:32:45,690 --> 00:32:47,240
I didn't feel warm there.

766
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:49,480
I mean warm inside.

767
00:32:50,420 --> 00:32:53,220
You'll understand after living there for a while.

768
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:56,350
No matter

769
00:32:56,370 --> 00:32:58,850
how bitter or upset you feel,

770
00:32:59,780 --> 00:33:01,300
there will be people by your side,

771
00:33:01,300 --> 00:33:02,250
loving you

772
00:33:02,510 --> 00:33:03,570
and caring for you.

773
00:33:04,070 --> 00:33:06,770
When you're happy, they're happy.

774
00:33:06,790 --> 00:33:07,790
When you're sad,

775
00:33:07,820 --> 00:33:09,920
they'll do everything to cheer you up,

776
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:12,380
staying up late at night to keep you company.

777
00:33:12,830 --> 00:33:15,190
Even if you had an iceberg in your heart,

778
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:17,200
they could make it melt away.

779
00:33:28,060 --> 00:33:29,950
They're your friends,

780
00:33:29,980 --> 00:33:31,550
not mine.

781
00:33:31,700 --> 00:33:33,290
You have friends like them,

782
00:33:33,310 --> 00:33:34,270
but I don't.

783
00:33:50,750 --> 00:33:53,110
What's mine will be yours too.

784
00:33:54,780 --> 00:33:56,360
But the condition is,

785
00:33:56,620 --> 00:33:58,550
you have to treat me as your sister.

786
00:33:59,030 --> 00:34:00,700
You don't just call me your sister;

787
00:34:00,700 --> 00:34:01,830
you accept me as one.

788
00:34:01,970 --> 00:34:03,100
Can you do that?

789
00:34:06,150 --> 00:34:07,830
If you can,

790
00:34:08,070 --> 00:34:09,870
I'll treat you as my brother too.

791
00:34:10,330 --> 00:34:11,250
A real one.

792
00:34:12,380 --> 00:34:13,960
I am your real brother.

793
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:15,670
So you know that, huh?

794
00:34:15,670 --> 00:34:16,429
It hurts.

795
00:34:17,630 --> 00:34:19,190
I pinched you too hard?

796
00:34:23,340 --> 00:34:24,560
I promise

797
00:34:24,580 --> 00:34:26,020
I'll never hit you again.

798
00:34:26,929 --> 00:34:27,780
Pinky swear.

799
00:34:29,100 --> 00:34:30,340
Pinky swear.

800
00:34:30,380 --> 00:34:33,440
Pinky swear. We'll never, ever break this promise.

801
00:34:37,770 --> 00:34:39,090
Can we go home now?

802
00:34:40,690 --> 00:34:41,690
Let's go.

803
00:34:56,850 --> 00:34:58,810
You went easy on him today.

804
00:34:58,830 --> 00:35:00,200
If he were my brother,

805
00:35:00,230 --> 00:35:03,310
I'd have beaten him so hard that he couldn't get out of bed.

806
00:35:03,310 --> 00:35:05,670
He's also your brother now.

807
00:35:11,600 --> 00:35:12,570
Fine.

808
00:35:14,110 --> 00:35:15,690
If you don't behave, I'll beat you to a pulp.

809
00:35:15,690 --> 00:35:17,580
Be gentle. He's sleeping.

810
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:35,750
Grandma, you're still up?

811
00:35:35,750 --> 00:35:37,030
Yeah. You found him?

812
00:35:37,060 --> 00:35:38,790
What happened? He fell asleep?

813
00:35:39,020 --> 00:35:40,800
Where did he go?

814
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:41,710
He went to find his mom.

815
00:35:41,710 --> 00:35:43,270
That was a long journey.

816
00:35:44,190 --> 00:35:45,820
Here, put him here.

817
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:47,660
Take off his shoes.

818
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:50,350
Naughty boy.

819
00:35:51,650 --> 00:35:52,370
Alright.

820
00:35:55,270 --> 00:35:56,490
Wanghe.

821
00:35:56,520 --> 00:35:57,600
We'll be going.

822
00:35:57,620 --> 00:35:58,350
Fenghua.

823
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:00,060
You must be hungry.

824
00:36:00,080 --> 00:36:00,980
I have some food here.

825
00:36:00,980 --> 00:36:02,190
Sit down and eat something. Come.

826
00:36:02,190 --> 00:36:03,470
It's okay, Grandma. He's not hungry.

827
00:36:03,470 --> 00:36:04,550
We'll be going.

828
00:36:04,550 --> 00:36:05,710
Get some rest.

829
00:36:05,910 --> 00:36:06,750
Thank you.

830
00:36:06,750 --> 00:36:07,630
See them out.

831
00:36:07,710 --> 00:36:08,710
Sorry.

832
00:36:08,770 --> 00:36:10,450
I caused you trouble today.

833
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:11,680
That's all?

834
00:36:12,510 --> 00:36:13,750
You'll buy me breakfast tomorrow.

835
00:36:13,750 --> 00:36:15,590
I want two extra tea eggs.

836
00:36:16,470 --> 00:36:17,190
Okay.

837
00:36:17,190 --> 00:36:18,120
Go get some rest.

838
00:36:29,910 --> 00:36:31,610
He's so naughty.

839
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,790
He really

840
00:36:34,830 --> 00:36:36,390
scared me to death.

841
00:36:37,050 --> 00:36:39,100
He's so bold.

842
00:36:37,470 --> 00:36:39,610
♫When the moon hangs in the sky♫

843
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:41,320
Just like you when you were little.

844
00:36:40,520 --> 00:36:42,280
♫And it's cooling in the yard♫

845
00:36:42,690 --> 00:36:45,420
♫Who is still by your side?♫

846
00:36:47,270 --> 00:36:51,000
♫As time passes♫

847
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:55,680
♫Is a lifetime really that long?♫

848
00:36:58,860 --> 00:37:00,190
Siyi.

849
00:36:59,120 --> 00:37:02,670
♫When youthful company fades, leaving only small talk and pleasantries♫

850
00:37:01,360 --> 00:37:02,710
Why are you awake?

851
00:37:03,230 --> 00:37:06,750
♫Spring feels short, while autumn lingers♫

852
00:37:03,250 --> 00:37:04,620
I'm scared.

853
00:37:06,100 --> 00:37:07,150
What are you scared of?

854
00:37:07,150 --> 00:37:07,840
The dark.

855
00:37:08,350 --> 00:37:12,400
♫A gentle breeze carries dreams away♫

856
00:37:08,990 --> 00:37:10,390
Then sleep with the light on.

857
00:37:10,390 --> 00:37:12,910
At home, I always slept with Mom.

858
00:37:13,610 --> 00:37:16,780
♫Dreams, sweet dreams♫

859
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:16,670
Alright. Come here then.

860
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:24,900
♫Life is long♫

861
00:37:23,190 --> 00:37:24,630
Don't toss and turn too much.

862
00:37:24,630 --> 00:37:25,990
I'm a light sleeper.

863
00:37:26,150 --> 00:37:26,820
Don't worry.

864
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:29,520
♫No need to dwell♫

865
00:37:26,980 --> 00:37:29,250
I won't move at all the whole night.

866
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:34,200
♫Like moonlight♫

867
00:37:35,510 --> 00:37:39,110
♫Don't forget♫

868
00:37:40,080 --> 00:37:43,190
♫Life is long♫

869
00:37:42,970 --> 00:37:44,380
Head up.

870
00:37:45,260 --> 00:37:48,300
♫No need to dwell♫

871
00:37:49,790 --> 00:37:52,980
♫Like moonlight♫

872
00:37:54,620 --> 00:37:58,180
♫The old times♫

873
00:37:57,970 --> 00:37:58,850
Siyi.

874
00:38:00,020 --> 00:38:01,280
What?

875
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:06,970
Is that boy tonight your boyfriend?

876
00:38:09,430 --> 00:38:11,430
The one who carried me into the room.

877
00:38:13,430 --> 00:38:15,230
So you weren't asleep in the car?

878
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:17,460
No. I was just too sleepy

879
00:38:17,500 --> 00:38:19,040
to open my eyes.

880
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:20,840
♫When the moon hangs in the sky♫

881
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:21,590
But I knew he was the one who carried me in.

882
00:38:21,610 --> 00:38:23,030
What's his name?

883
00:38:21,830 --> 00:38:23,250
♫And it's cooling in the yard♫

884
00:38:23,990 --> 00:38:27,010
♫Who is still by your side?♫

885
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:26,410
His name is Xie Wanghe.

886
00:38:26,790 --> 00:38:28,580
You should call him Brother Wanghe.

887
00:38:28,490 --> 00:38:31,960
♫As time passes♫

888
00:38:28,900 --> 00:38:30,820
Are you two close?

889
00:38:31,730 --> 00:38:33,420
Can you just go to sleep?

890
00:38:33,130 --> 00:38:36,670
♫Is a lifetime really that long?♫

891
00:38:39,850 --> 00:38:43,700
♫When youthful company fades, leaving only small talk and pleasantries♫

892
00:38:44,390 --> 00:38:47,910
♫Spring feels short, while autumn lingers♫

893
00:38:48,260 --> 00:38:49,790
Wanghe

894
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:53,430
♫A gentle breeze carries dreams away♫

895
00:38:49,820 --> 00:38:51,060
is a really nice guy,

896
00:38:51,080 --> 00:38:52,480
very righteous.

897
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:54,620
So you should be polite to him.

898
00:38:54,360 --> 00:38:58,280
♫Dreamland and dreams♫

899
00:38:54,640 --> 00:38:55,570
No problem.

900
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:58,440
I'll just call him my brother-in-law when I see him again.

901
00:38:58,440 --> 00:38:59,970
What are you talking about?

902
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,520
What's going on

903
00:39:01,550 --> 00:39:02,910
in that little head of yours?

904
00:39:02,850 --> 00:39:06,060
♫Life is long♫

905
00:39:03,070 --> 00:39:04,270
Mom said

906
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:07,400
people don't be nice to others for no reason.

907
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:10,440
♫No need to dwell♫

908
00:39:07,550 --> 00:39:09,680
They always want something in return.

909
00:39:11,310 --> 00:39:12,440
It's just her.

910
00:39:12,010 --> 00:39:15,300
♫Like moonlight♫

911
00:39:12,470 --> 00:39:13,660
She's selfish herself,

912
00:39:13,660 --> 00:39:15,860
so she thinks everyone else is the same.

913
00:39:16,410 --> 00:39:17,290
Don't worry.

914
00:39:17,030 --> 00:39:20,510
♫Don't forget♫

915
00:39:17,720 --> 00:39:20,320
Everyone in this yard is very nice.

916
00:39:20,910 --> 00:39:22,700
You'll see that as time goes by.

917
00:39:21,710 --> 00:39:24,790
♫Life is long♫

918
00:39:22,740 --> 00:39:23,790
Go to sleep now.

919
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:29,190
♫No need to dwell♫

920
00:39:31,340 --> 00:39:34,580
♫Like moonlight♫

921
00:39:35,910 --> 00:39:39,360
♫The old times♫

922
00:39:39,140 --> 00:39:45,890
[Breakfast]

923
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:44,230
Ge Siwei.

924
00:39:46,280 --> 00:39:48,440
All new students get bullied,

925
00:39:48,790 --> 00:39:50,830
especially skinny, little ones like you

926
00:39:50,830 --> 00:39:51,810
who look fragile.

927
00:39:51,810 --> 00:39:52,960
You're the easiest target.

928
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:54,240
Don't scare him.

929
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:55,560
Don't listen to his nonsense.

930
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:57,110
If someone tries to beat you, tell the teacher.

931
00:39:57,110 --> 00:39:57,840
Siwei,

932
00:39:57,860 --> 00:39:58,700
it's useless.

933
00:39:58,850 --> 00:39:59,660
If you tell the teacher,

934
00:39:59,660 --> 00:40:00,510
they'll beat you up even harder afterward.

935
00:40:00,510 --> 00:40:01,770
A vicious cycle.

936
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:04,260
Siyi.

937
00:40:05,250 --> 00:40:06,450
She's a girl.

938
00:40:06,460 --> 00:40:07,470
She's never been beaten up.

939
00:40:07,470 --> 00:40:09,400
You should listen to me about this.

940
00:40:09,790 --> 00:40:11,110
If someone beats you,

941
00:40:11,110 --> 00:40:12,550
don't fight back.

942
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:13,840
Why?

943
00:40:14,150 --> 00:40:15,630
If someone hits you,

944
00:40:15,910 --> 00:40:17,920
just fall when they push you

945
00:40:18,230 --> 00:40:19,110
and then start twitching

946
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:20,300
and foaming at the mouth.

947
00:40:20,300 --> 00:40:21,830
Can't you teach him something good?

948
00:40:21,830 --> 00:40:22,710
If you teach him to fake injuries at such a young age,

949
00:40:22,710 --> 00:40:23,970
how can he grow up to be a good man?

950
00:40:23,970 --> 00:40:25,500
This trick works well.

951
00:40:25,640 --> 00:40:27,480
I used it against Liang before.

952
00:40:27,510 --> 00:40:28,290
You have no idea.

953
00:40:28,290 --> 00:40:29,290
The boy called Liang

954
00:40:29,290 --> 00:40:32,150
nearly got beaten into a cripple by his dad that day.

955
00:40:33,870 --> 00:40:35,150
Are we clear?

956
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:37,040
If someone pushes you,

957
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:38,660
you roll your eyes first.

958
00:40:39,250 --> 00:40:40,420
How do I do that?

959
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,910
Why don't you show me?

960
00:40:44,130 --> 00:40:45,170
Do it!

961
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:47,970
Do it, do it, do it!

962
00:40:48,010 --> 00:40:50,590
Do it, do it, do it!

963
00:40:51,310 --> 00:40:52,710
Be quiet.

964
00:40:52,710 --> 00:40:54,130
You're the new kid,

965
00:40:54,400 --> 00:40:55,870
aren't you?

966
00:40:58,650 --> 00:40:59,750
Are you okay?

967
00:41:00,130 --> 00:41:01,230
Are you okay?

968
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:03,660
Are you alright?

969
00:41:04,550 --> 00:41:05,970
Are you okay?

970
00:41:08,210 --> 00:41:09,500
Here we are.

971
00:41:09,830 --> 00:41:10,830
Good morning.

972
00:41:10,850 --> 00:41:12,010
Good morning, miss. Good morning, sir.

973
00:41:12,010 --> 00:41:12,810
Hey.

974
00:41:15,760 --> 00:41:16,840
Siyi, I'm leaving.

975
00:41:16,870 --> 00:41:17,550
Okay.

976
00:41:20,950 --> 00:41:22,380
Roll your eyes and twitch,

977
00:41:22,380 --> 00:41:23,260
remember?

978
00:41:25,500 --> 00:41:27,350
Stop. He's just a kid.

979
00:41:27,350 --> 00:41:30,280
What if he really tries to scam someone in the future?

980
00:41:31,390 --> 00:41:32,390
Brother-in-law.

981
00:41:33,810 --> 00:41:35,470
Be nice to my sister,

982
00:41:35,490 --> 00:41:37,090
or I'll beat you up.

983
00:41:40,740 --> 00:41:42,260
Who are you calling your brother-in-law?

984
00:41:42,260 --> 00:41:42,970
He's crazy.

985
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:45,530
I'll have to give him a beating again tonight.

986
00:42:01,140 --> 00:42:02,620
Why do you think

987
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:04,860
Siwei

988
00:42:05,170 --> 00:42:07,950
called Wanghe his brother-in-law?

989
00:42:10,240 --> 00:42:11,430
What's wrong?

990
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:15,090
Are you jealous?

991
00:42:15,110 --> 00:42:17,140
Why would I be jealous?

992
00:42:17,470 --> 00:42:19,070
I just think it was funny.

993
00:42:21,450 --> 00:42:22,810
Don't worry.

994
00:42:24,780 --> 00:42:26,290
Xie Wanghe and Ma Siyi

995
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:27,380
can't be together.

996
00:42:29,160 --> 00:42:29,870
Why?

997
00:42:29,910 --> 00:42:30,980
Wanghe said that

998
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:33,350
for a man to have a successful career,

999
00:42:33,350 --> 00:42:36,010
he needs a helpful wife first.

1000
00:42:36,030 --> 00:42:37,260
Given Ma Siyi's situation,

1001
00:42:37,260 --> 00:42:39,860
it'd be good enough if she didn't hold him back.

1002
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:43,510
You can't say that.

1003
00:42:43,560 --> 00:42:46,270
Why would Siyi hold him back?

1004
00:42:48,180 --> 00:42:49,520
We're all friends.

1005
00:42:49,630 --> 00:42:53,160
Don't make it sound like I'm speaking ill of her behind her back.

1006
00:42:57,460 --> 00:42:59,190
You don't have a chance either.

1007
00:42:59,560 --> 00:43:00,640
Why not?

1008
00:43:02,700 --> 00:43:04,020
You're too silly.

1009
00:43:06,340 --> 00:43:08,420
Shao Xingchi!

